</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="678">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="678">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182025" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprina">cuprina</taxonomicName>
, of copper, referring to the color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="678">
Diagnosis A small, reddish yellow species belonging to a group of ambiguous species composing the &quot; 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33648" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole carapuna Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole carapuna Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carapuna">carapuna</taxonomicName>
complex&quot; (see list in heading above), close to the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group and possibly better placed there. All are relatively small in size, with the major possessing a reduced mesonotal convexity, as well as cephalic sculpturing that consists entirely of longitudinal carinulae extending to or almost to the occipital border seen in full face. All also have a minor with a broad, concave occiput, which lacks a collar. Among these species, P. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182025" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprina">cuprina</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33648" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole carapuna Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole carapuna Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carapuna">carapuna</taxonomicName>
but distinguished from it by color and the absence of foveolation on the postpetiolar node of the major and posterior three-fourths of the dorsal head surface of the minor. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.02, HL 1.16, SL 0.58, EL 0.16, PW 0.56. Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.66, SL 0.56, EL 0.12, PW 0.38. color Major and minor: concolorous medium yellow, with slight reddish tinge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="678">
Range I have seen an additional series of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182025" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cuprina Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="678" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprina">cuprina</taxonomicName>
from Tingo Maria, Madre de Dios, Peru, collected by W. L. Brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="678">biology The type colony was found in terra firme forest nesting in a rotten branch on the litter surface of the ground. It comprised a</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="678">single queen and several hundred workers (Stefan Cover, personal communication).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
